<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="while-conj">while <strong><em>conj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /waɪl/    美 /waɪl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>当...的时候；和...同时；在...时：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Never get on or off a bus while it is moving.
公共汽车没停稳时千万不要上下车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Would you look after the children while I do the shopping? 
我买东西的时候你能不能照看一下孩子？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I hurt my leg while playing football.
我踢足球时把腿弄伤了。</p><footer>外研② – 1</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[表示对比] 然而：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was never very neat, while my roommate Kate was extremely organized.
我从来不是一个很爱整洁的人，而我的室友凯特却极有条理。</p><footer>2014 重庆</footer></div>

<h4 id="3-although">3.★ <strong>虽然；尽管 (although)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>While online shopping has changed our life, not all of its effects have been positive.
尽管网上购物已经改变了我们的生活，但并非它所有的影响都是正面的。</p><footer>2016 浙江</footer></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>只要：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>While there’s life there’s hope.
只要活着就有希望。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Give your body and brain a rest by stepping outside for<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ while, exercising, or doing something you enjoy.
  （2016 全国）  </li>
<li><strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (尽管) the students came from different countries, they got along quite well in the summer camp.  （2015 福建改）  </li>
<li>There’s no way of knowing why one man makes an important discovery <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ another man, also intelligent, fails.  （2013 全国）<br />
A.since<br />
B.if<br />
C.as<br />
D.while  </li>
<li>Mary made coffee <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ her guests were finishing their meal.  （2010 全国改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. a  2. While / Although / Though  3. D  4. while  </p></div>